title.narrative: STRENGTHENED LOCAL GOVERNANCE

description.narrative: Government and local authorities have strengthened capacities and skills to operationalize key policies and frameworks to address child deprivations and are held accountable for delivering of quality and resilient, child-friendly services., which contributes to Access To Justice, Child Health, Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children (Covid), Children In Urban Settings / Local Governance, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Girls and boys grow up in resilient, inclusive and child friendly communities, that are supported by enabling environment and systems that provide an equitable chance in life.

description.narrative: The National Children Commission Bill was passed by Parliament and assented to by the President in April. This represents a significant milestone for children's rights in Malawi with the law enabling the establishment of a Commission to facilitate multi-sectoral coordination of children's issues and programs across ministries and departments to ensure implementation of children's rights. UNICEF's strategic budget advocacy has resulted in notable increases in budget allocations to interventions that matter for the well-being of children such as immunization and social cash transfers. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/12/2019
